  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "An \"Add-On Item\" on Amazon refers to a product that is typically low-priced and designed to be purchased in conjunction with other items in a larger order. These items usually require customers to meet a minimum order value to include them in their purchase. The primary purpose of Add-On Items is to optimize shipping efficiency and reduce costs by bundling smaller products with larger orders.\n\n### Key Features of Add-On Items:\n\n1. **Minimum Purchase Requirement**: To purchase an Add-On Item, your total order must usually meet a specified minimum amount (commonly around $25, though this can vary). This ensures that the cost of shipping the item is justified by the overall order size.\n\n2. **Low-Cost Products**: Add-On Items are often inexpensive accessories, consumables, or small essentials that complement larger purchases. Examples might include batteries, phone cases, or household supplies.\n\n3. **Exclusive to Amazon Marketplace**: Not all sellers on Amazon offer Add-On Items. These products are typically provided by Amazon itself or by select sellers who have opted into the Add-On program.\n\n4. **Shipping Efficiency**: By encouraging the purchase of additional items alongside other products, Amazon can streamline packaging and shipping processes, making it more cost-effective for both the company and the customer.\n\n5. **Visibility**: Add-On Items are usually labeled as such on product pages. Additionally, they might appear as suggestions during the checkout process when your cart meets the minimum order threshold.\n\n### Benefits for Customers:\n\n- **Convenience**: Easily add essential, low-cost items to your existing orders without needing to make a separate purchase.\n- **Cost-Effective Shipping**: Combine Add-On Items with other purchases to benefit from Amazon\u2019s shipping options, including free shipping for eligible orders.\n\n### How to Purchase Add-On Items:\n\n1. **Add to Cart**: Browse Amazon and select an Add-On Item you wish to purchase.\n2. **Meet Minimum Order**: Ensure that your total cart value meets or exceeds the required minimum (e.g., $25).\n3. **Check Eligibility**: Some Add-On Items are only available for certain shipping options or regions, so verify that your order qualifies.\n4. **Proceed to Checkout**: Complete your purchase as usual, with the Add-On Item included in your order.\n\n### Example Scenario:\n\nSuppose you\u2019re buying a book priced at $20. You want to add a pack of bookmarks priced at $5 as an Add-On Item. Since the combined total ($25) meets the minimum requirement, you can include the bookmarks in your purchase without incurring additional shipping costs specifically for the bookmarks.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nAdd-On Items are a convenient feature on Amazon that allows customers to include low-cost accessories or essentials with their primary purchases, provided they meet a minimum order value. This system benefits both Amazon and shoppers by enhancing shipping efficiency and offering a wider range of products within a single transaction.",
